This page documents published academic research about Emacs. All disciplines are relevant, in lexical order by the first author, across all disciplines.

There is also a Zotero group called [https://www.zotero.org/groups/2392126/emacs/ Emacs].

Thanks to contributors on [https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/djrlib/academic_research_about_emacs/ /r/emacs] and [https://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/53236/academic-research-about-emacs Emacs StackExchange site].

== List of published academic research about Emacs ==

Aspinall, David. (2000). [http://proofgeneral.inf.ed.ac.uk/papers/pgoutline.ps.gz Proof General: A Generic Tool for Proof Development]. In /Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems/ (TACAS'00), LNCS 1785.  Plus a few related articles at https://proofgeneral.github.io/pubs/

Corallo, Andrea; Nassi, Luca; Manca, Nicola.  (2020).  [https://zenodo.org/record/3736363 Bringing GNU Emacs to Native Code]. 13th European Lisp Symposium (ELS 2020) (ELS'20), Zurich, 27-28 April 2020.

Crestani, Marcus.  (2005).  [http://crestani.de/xemacs/pdf/thesis-newgc.pdf A New Garbage Collector for XEmacs].  Masters thesis, Univertät Tübingen.

Houser, Chris and Kalter, Scott D.  (1992).  [https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/147135.147248 Eoops: an object-oriented programming system for Emacs-Lisp].  SIGPLAN Lisp Pointers 5(3), pp 25-33.

Lapalme, Guy.  (1998).  [https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/ab48/0568f9a0e4a6fc3b25918c1a481bb1b99c37.pdf Dynamic Tabbing for Automatic Indentation with the Layout Rule].  Journal of Functional Programming (JFP), 8(5), pp 493-502.

Monnier, Stefan and Sperber, Michael. (2020). [https://dl.acm.org/doi/abs/10.1145/3386324
Evolution of Emacs Lisp]. /ACM HOPL'2020/.

Monnier, Stefan. (2020). [https://programming-journal.org/2021/5/1/
SMIE: Weakness is Power! Auto-indentation with incomplete information]. 
 <Programming> Journal, Volume 5, issue 1.

Monnier, Stefan. (2022). [https://zenodo.org/record/6228797 Open Closures: Disclosing lambda's inner monomaniac object!]. ELS'2022.

Neubauer, Matthias and Sperber, Michael. (2001). [http://www.deinprogramm.de/sperber/papers/dynamic-scope-analysis.pdf Down with Emacs Lisp: Dynamic Scope Analysis].  In /International Conference on Functional Programming/ (ICFP'01), pp 38-49.

Palmer, J.; Duffy, T.; Gomoll, K; Gomoll, T.; Richards-Palmquist. J. and Trumble, J. A. (1988). [https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/6920/references The design and evaluation of online help for Unix EMACS: capturing the user in menu design], in /IEEE Transactions on Professional Communication/, vol. 31, no. 1, pp. 44-51, March 1988. doi:10.1109/47.6920.

Stallman, R. M. (1981). [https://doi.org/10.1145/800209.806466 EMACS the Extensible, Customizable Self-documenting Display Editor]. /Proceedings of the ACM SIGPLAN SIGOA Symposium on Text Manipulation/, 147–156.

Twidale, Michael B.; Jones, M. Cameron. (2005). [https://www.ideals.illinois.edu/handle/2142/9607 "Let them use emacs": the interaction of simplicity and appropriation]. /International reports on socio-informatics/ 2(2) 66-71.

Verna, Dider.  (2010).  [https://hal.archives-ouvertes.fr/hal-01543381/ CLOX: Common Lisp Objects for XEmacs].  European Lisp Symposium (ELS) 2010.

Zhong, Shudan and Xu, Hong. (2019). [https://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=3301275.3302272 Intelligently recommending key bindings on physical keyboards with demonstrations in Emacs]. In /Proceedings of the 24th International Conference on Intelligent User Interfaces/ (IUI), 12–17. doi:10.1145/3301275.3302272.

== Other research of unclear academic publication status ==

Voit, K. (2013). [http://arxiv.org/abs/1304.1332 What really happened on September 15th 2008? Getting The Most from Your Personal Information with Memacs]. ArXiv:1304.1332 [Cs].
